name: Northeast Health Services
directions: When you enter the waiting room, grab a key for your preferred rest room (they are gendered) and go through the door across from the keys. The rest rooms are behind that door and are marked with signs. People can also help at the front desk if you are unsure where the bathrooms are.
comment: There is a large population on LGBTQ+ people who go to this mental health facility. The staff are very nice and accommodating. However, in the men's room there is some racist graffiti which I have brought to there attention. It should be removed shortly.

name: 3-D Guitar's & Music
directions: The music store is small. The bathrooms are on the wall near the entrance
comment: The bathrooms do have gender signs on them. However, the employees do not care which one you go into. I go to the music store often. I am not out to most of the employees. No employee has ever batted an eye on which bathroom I use. The store has a very safe environment.

name: Silver Lake Regional High School
directions: From the event enterance (marked by a sign), go straight the hallway near the music room. Right before you go see the music room. There is a single stall gender neutral bathroom. It is marked by a red sign labeled "All Gender Restroom".
comment: The bathroom is very clean. It used to be a faculty bathroom. Because if the school's GSA, students and visitors can be comfortable in the bathroom. However, during plays/musicals, this section may be blocked off for cast and crew to use for consuming.

comment: There is no key for either one, just knock. Busy brunch place (and maybe other times), probably easy to use without buying food. One men's room and one women's room, single stall and accessible.

name: Wydział Nauk Społecznych, UAM
directions: There are three accessible restrooms there that I know of: In building D, the -1 floor, next to the elevator; in building AB, corridor to the left near the main entrance; in building AB, corridor in front of the main entrance, next to the elevator.
comment: You can easily sneak in pretending to be a student. May not be available during holidays, but regular weekends shouldn't be a problem. If you don't speak Polish and someone asks what you're doing there, just say you're from the Erasmus programme.

name: Mauhaus Cat Cafe and Lounge
directions: Two small unisex bathrooms to the immediate left of the coffee counter.
comment: Mauhaus is a reservations-recommended place to have a cup of beverage and possibly a pastry while spending an hour in the company of friendly felines.  Walk-ins may have a long wait to get time with the cats but can order a beverage and pee and observe the kitties through the large window.  Friendly staff.  Please make a small purchase if you stop in, they operate on a shoestring.

name: Game Nite
directions: Two restrooms in the store, one near the front, one by the gaming rooms (head right into the retail section, bathroom is halfway down that section on the left wall.
comment: Game Nite is a "friendly local game store" about half retail space and half "grab a table and play a game" space.  Awesome place to hang out.  Safe place to pee.  The store manager has a trans kid.
